<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em> Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow, back on Thursday. Unless. You know.</em></p><tab=
le class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellpaddi=
ng=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Oh Elon</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk is the richest person in the=
 world, and an active Twitter user. When he tweets, he gets a lot of spammy=
 replies, many of which seem to be written by automated bots. He has compla=
ined about this a lot. Eventually he decided to do something about it. The =
thing that he decided to do about it was=C2=A0<em>buy Twitter</em>. On Apri=
l 13, he <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.=
259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE0MTgwOTEv=
MDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQ1NjQxL3RtMjIxMjc0OGQxX3NjMTNkYS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB6a515b31" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">sent a letter</a> to Twitter Inc.=E2=80=99s board o=
f directors offering to buy the company for $54.20 per share in cash. =E2=
=80=9CIf our twitter bid succeeds,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9lbG9ub=
XVzay9zdGF0dXMvMTUxNzIxNTA2NjU1MDExNjM1NA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdcd1a471=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;">he tweeted</a>,=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cwe will defeat the spam bots or die=
 trying!=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">His Twitter bid succeeded=
. On April 25, Twitter and Musk issued a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZl=
cy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTE3NzIwL2QzMTkxOTBkZXg5OTEuaHR=
t/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBeea032ec" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">joint press release</a> announ=
cing that he had agreed to buy Twitter for $54.20 per share. The press rele=
ase included a quote from Musk promising to =E2=80=9Cmake Twitter better=E2=
=80=9D by, among other things, =E2=80=9Cdefeating the spam bots.=E2=80=9D H=
e was really mad at the spam bots! He wanted to buy Twitter because of the =
spam bots.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yesterday he announced that he d=
oes not want to buy Twitter=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMTcvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXNheXMtdHdpdHRlci1tdXN0LXByb3ZlLWJvdC1=
jbGFpbXMtZm9yLWRlYWwtdG8tcHJvY2VlZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNTE3MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG=
1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA1MTcmdXRtX=
2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB308ad429" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">becau=
se of the spam bots</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon M=
usk declared he won=E2=80=99t proceed with his $44 billion takeover of Twit=
ter Inc. unless the social media giant can prove bots make up fewer than 5%=
 of its users, casting yet more uncertainty over the deal.</p><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">The billionaire tweeted =E2=80=9Cthis deal cannot move forw=
ard=E2=80=9D unless Twitter provides proof of its claims, reiterating his o=
wn view that the ratio is far higher. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">Twitter said it is =E2=80=9Ccommitted to completing the transaction on=
 the agreed price and terms as promptly as practicable,=E2=80=9D in a state=
ment on Tuesday. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The battle over =
bots has become a sticking point for Musk, who told a tech conference in Mi=
ami on Monday that fake users make up at least 20% of all Twitter accounts,=
 possibly as high as 90%. Twitter regularly states in its quarterly results=
 that the average of false or spam accounts =E2=80=9Crepresented fewer than=
 5% of our monthly daily active users during the quarter,=E2=80=9D adding t=
hat it applied =E2=80=9Csignificant judgment=E2=80=9D to its estimate, and =
the true number could be higher.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">I think it is important to be clear here that=C2=A0<em>Musk is lying</em=
>. The spam bots are not why he is backing away from the deal, as you can t=
ell from the fact that the spam bots are why he=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>the =
deal.=C2=A0He has produced no evidence at all that Twitter=E2=80=99s estima=
tes are wrong, and certainly not that they are <em>materially</em> wrong or=
 made=C2=A0in bad faith. (Musk can only get out of the deal if Twitter's fi=
lings are wrong <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27=
745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwM=
jItMDUtMTMvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXRyb2xscy10d2l0dGVyP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA1MTcyMl9NT05FWVNU=
VUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDU=
xNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8faedb1b" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;"> in a way that would cause</a> a =E2=80=9Cmaterial adverse effect=E2=80=
=9D on Twitter, which is vanishingly unlikely.) His own <a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iY=
y5jb20vMjAyMi8wNS8xNC9lbG9uLW11c2staGFzLXdyb25nLWFwcHJvYWNoLXRvLWNvdW50LWZh=
a2VzLXNwYW0tb24tdHdpdHRlci1leHBlcnRzLmh0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9d7f71=
80" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">supposed methodology</a> for counting spam bots is laughable. =
Yesterday Twitter=E2=80=99s chief executive officer, Parag Agrawal, <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6L=
y90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9wYXJhZ2Evc3RhdHVzLzE1MjYyMzc1ODA2Mzg4NTkyNjc/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cB9ae975fa" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;"> tweeted a thread</a> explaining in general =
terms=C2=A0how Twitter estimates that fake accounts represent fewer than 5%=
 of its count of active users, and how this analysis can=E2=80=99t be easil=
y replicated by outsiders (because they don=E2=80=99t know which accounts a=
re real, and also because they don=E2=80=99t know which accounts Twitter <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0=
cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9wYXJhZ2Evc3RhdHVzLzE1MjYyMzc1ODk1MzQ5NTM0NzI/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB6e7b2e11" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> counts as daily active users</a>). It =
