om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">The merger proxy</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In that vein, this morning Twitter cal=
mly filed the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2774=
5071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTE=
vMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTUyMjUwL2QyODMxMTlkcHJlbTE0YS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cBf886f8d5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;">preliminary=C2=A0proxy statement</a> for its deal with=
 Musk, a key step toward getting shareholder approval. In general, the most=
 interesting part of a merger proxy is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy=
9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTUyMjUwL2QyODMxMTlkcHJlbTE0YS5od=
G0jdG9jMjgzMTE5XzUx/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB992a91b2" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the =E2=80=
=9CBackground of the Merger=E2=80=9D section</a>, which describes in detail=
 how the deal was negotiated and what the board of directors was thinking, =
and that is true here.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One fun thing to do =
with this proxy is to go through it and count how many times Musk violated =
US securities laws in his efforts to buy Twitter. For instance:</p><blockqu=
ote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also on March 26, 2022, Mr. Musk contacted=
 Egon Durban, one of Twitter=E2=80=99s directors, to set up a discussion be=
tween Mr. Musk and Mr. Durban. Mr. Musk and Mr. Durban subsequently spoke o=
n March 26, 2022 and March 27, 2022 and discussed the potential of Mr. Musk=
 joining the Twitter Board, as well as the fact that Mr. Musk had purchased=
 a significant stake of more than five percent of our common stock.=C2=A0 =
=E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On March 27, 2022, Messrs. Musk, =
[the chairman of Twitter=E2=80=99s board of directors, Bret] Taylor and [Tw=
itter Chief Executive Officer Parag] Agrawal discussed Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s i=
nterest in Twitter and potentially joining the Twitter Board. As part of th=
at discussion, Mr. Musk stated that he was considering various options with=
 respect to his ownership, including potentially joining the Twitter Board,=
 seeking to take Twitter private or starting a competitor to Twitter.</p></=
blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk started <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdv=
di9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQyODYzL3RtMjIxMTc=
1N2QxX3NjMTNkLmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdf7ad80d" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">buying Twitt=
er stock</a> in late January, and crossed over 5% on March 14. Under the se=
curities laws, he <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzI0MC4=
xM2QtMQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3a1ebba1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">had 10 days</a> =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0until March 24 =E2=80=94=C2=A0to disclose this fact publicly. In f=
act he <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.25=
9617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMT=
EwNDY1OTIyMDQxOTExLzAwMDExMDQ2NTktMjItMDQxOTExLWluZGV4Lmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB1e67d65c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">waited until April 4</a>, disclosing his stak=
e 11 days late. During this period =E2=80=94=C2=A0when he was legally requi=
red to disclose his Twitter stake, but had not =E2=80=94=C2=A0he (1) kept b=
uying more stock and (2)=C2=A0<em>had discussions with Twitter=E2=80=99s bo=
ard of directors about taking over the company</em>. That seems like it wou=
ld have been material information, for the people who were selling him the =
stock!</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Then, when he finally did disclose h=
is stake on April 4, he <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhL=
zE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQxOTExL3RtMjIxMTQ4MmQxX3NjMTNnLmh0bQ/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cBb4e16f6e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;">did it on a form</a> (Schedule 13G) that =
is limited to passive investors, checking a box <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lb=
GwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzI0MC4xM2QtMQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC3a1ebba1" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;">indicating that he had</a> =E2=80=9Cnot acquired the securities with =
any purpose, or with the effect, of changing or influencing the control of =
the issuer.=E2=80=9D Again, he was=C2=A0<em>already in discussions about ta=
king over Twitter or joining its board</em>. He was very much not eligible =
to use Schedule 13G, and by using 13G =E2=80=94=C2=A0and representing he ha=
d no plans to influence the company=E2=80=99s control =E2=80=94=C2=A0he was=
 lying to the US Securities and Exchange Commission and the market.</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Then Musk negotiated a board seat and standstill w=
ith Twitter, which was made public; he <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy=
9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIyMDQyODYzL3RtMjIxMTc1N2QxX3NjMTNkL=
mh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCdf7ad80d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">filed a Schedule 13D</a>=
, belatedly but accurately indicating that he was going to be an active inv=
estor. The 13D said that, while he was keeping his options open, he had =E2=
=80=9Cno present plans or intentions=E2=80=9D to take Twitter private. A fe=
w days later he decided to scrap the standstill agreement and buy Twitter i=
nstead; again from the merger proxy=E2=80=99s background section:</p><block=
quote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On April 9, 2022, before Mr. Musk=E2=80=
=99s appointment to the Twitter Board became effective, Mr. Musk notified M=
essrs. Taylor and Agrawal that he would not be joining the Twitter Board an=
d would be making an offer to take Twitter private. Mr. Agrawal informed th=
e members of the Twitter Board of Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s communication.</p></bl=
ockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That was a Saturday; that Monday, Mus=
k <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTEwNDY=
1OTIyMDQ0NDgxL3RtMjIxMjQyMmQxX3NjMTNkYS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB907d4=
2d3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">filed an amended Schedule 13D</a> announcing that he was not j=
oining the board. This 13D said that he =E2=80=9Cmight engage in discussion=
s with the Board=E2=80=9D about =E2=80=9Cpotential business combinations,=
=E2=80=9D but neglected to mention that he had already told Twitter he woul=
d be making an offer.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know;=
 it all seems bad. The SEC is supposedly =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9=
hcnRpY2xlcy9lbG9uLW11c2tzLWJlbGF0ZWQtZGlzY2xvc3VyZS1vZi10d2l0dGVyLXN0YWtlLX=
RyaWdnZXJzLXJlZ3VsYXRvcnMtcHJvYmVzLTExNjUyMzAzODk0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
B654988b1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">investigating</a>=E2=80=9D Musk=E2=80=99s disclosure fai=
lures in this deal, and I suppose these admissions will help with the inves=
tigation, but what can they do about it? Fine him? He's so rich. Prevent hi=
m from buying Twitter? That=E2=80=99s what he wants! Ban him from running a=
 public company? That is probably more drastic than the SEC (or a judge) co=
uld stomach, and will just lead to another annoying effort to take Tesla pr=
ivate.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway the merger proxy also d=
oes give some insight into Twitter's board deliberations. For one thing, th=
e board called big Twitter shareholders=C2=A0and seems to have gotten a pre=
tty clear message of =E2=80=9Cjust take the deal=E2=80=9D:</p><blockquote><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Over the subsequent four days [after April 17],=
 Messrs. Taylor and [Twitter director Patrick] Pichette held meetings with =
a number of Twitter=E2=80=99s largest institutional stockholders to discuss=
 the perspectives of these stockholders on Mr.=C2=A0Musk=E2=80=99s acquisit=
ion proposal and Twitter more generally. As part of these meetings, these T=
witter stockholders generally (1) expressed that Twitter has much opportuni=
ty, but indicated a perceived failure of historical execution; (2) expresse=
d understanding there has been recent management change and openness to a s=
tand-alone plan to give them confidence in the long term; and (3) encourage=
d the Twitter Board to seriously consider Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s proposal and w=
eigh the risks of future execution.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">The board also heard from its financial advisers that $54.20 wa=
s pretty good. (In hindsight, tech stocks fell after they signed the deal, =
and it looks even better.) The proxy summarizes the fairness opinions of Tw=
itter's advisers at <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0M=
TgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTUyMjUwL2QyODMxMTlkcHJlbTE0YS5odG0jdG9jMjgzMTE5XzUz=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBab4a20e1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Goldman Sachs Group Inc.</a> an=
d <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzE=
yNTIyMTUyMjUwL2QyODMxMTlkcHJlbTE0YS5odG0jdG9jMjgzMTE5XzU0/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cBa0c9a4b8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co.</a>, which included, for=
 instance, discounted cash flow valuations of $36.50 (the bottom of JPMorga=
n=E2=80=99s=C2=A0range) to $60.90 (the top of Goldman=E2=80=99s). The proxy=
 also includes Twitter=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdh=
ci9kYXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTUyMjUwL2QyODMxMTlkcHJlbTE0YS5odG0jdG9=
jMjgzMTE5XzU1/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2fbf9802" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">management financi=
al projections</a> for the next few years, which included growing revenue f=
rom $5.9 billion in 2022 to $12.9 billion in 2027, and growing unlevered fr=
ee cash flow from $561 million to $3.7 billion. (Musk=E2=80=99s own <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8wNS8wNi90ZWNobm9sb2d5L2Vsb24tbXVzay10d2l0dGVy=
LXBpdGNoLWRlY2suaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB177792a3" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">pitch to =
co-investors</a> in his Twitter buyout projected revenue of $26.4 billion a=
nd free cash flow of $9.4 billion=C2=A0by 2028, so I guess he is more ambit=
ious.)</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The board did=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em=
>contact other potential buyers, on the theory that (1) =E2=80=9CMr. Musk=
=E2=80=99s acquisition proposal had been publicly disclosed (and the subjec=
t of significant press coverage),=E2=80=9D so if anyone else wanted to buy =
Twitter they would know to call Twitter, (2) there probably weren=E2=80=99t=
 any other realistic buyers and (3) trying to find another buyer might scar=
e off Musk. Given the shareholder feedback (to take the deal), the analyses=
 of Twitter's financial advisers (that $54.20 was a pretty good price), and=
 =E2=80=9Cthe recent general decline in trading prices of social media comp=
anies,=E2=80=9D the board figured that $54.20 was the best they were going =
to do, so they tried to pin down the deal with Musk.</p><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">In doing this they were =E2=80=94=C2=A0or at least, the merger pr=
oxy now says they were =E2=80=94=C2=A0properly focused on making sure that =
Musk was actually committed to closing the deal:</p><blockquote><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">Throughout the remainder of April 24, 2022, and into Apri=
l 25, 2022, Twitter, Parent and Mr. Musk and their respective legal advisor=
s negotiated the terms of the merger agreement and related transaction docu=
ments. Key terms negotiated between the parties included (1) Twitter=E2=80=
=99s specific enforcement rights to require Parent and Mr. Musk to perform =
their obligations under the merger agreement and consummate the closing on =
the terms set forth in the merger agreement, as well as third-party benefic=
iary rights under the equity commitment letter to enforce Mr. Musk=E2=80=99=
s obligations to fund the equity commitment; (2) the circumstances in which=
 a termination fee would be payable by Parent and Mr. Musk and the amount o=
f the termination fee; (3) the availability of potential monetary damages u=
nder the merger agreement; (4) the terms and conditions applicable to Paren=
t=E2=80=99s and Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s obligations to obtain regulatory approva=
ls, and the closing conditions related to regulatory approvals; (5) the ter=
ms and conditions applicable to Parent=E2=80=99s and Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s obl=
igations to complete debt financing arrangements for the acquisition, and T=
witter=E2=80=99s obligations to assist Parent and Mr. Musk in such efforts;=
 =E2=80=A6</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the section titl=
ed =E2=80=9CReasons for the Merger,=E2=80=9D the proxy adds that one reason=
 the board agreed to the deal is:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;"><em>Reasonable Likelihood of Consummation. </em>The belief of the Twitte=
r Board that an acquisition by Mr. Musk has a reasonable likelihood of clos=
ing. In that regard, the Twitter Board considered Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s busine=
ss reputation and financial resources, as well as those of Parent=E2=80=99s=
 debt financing sources, which the Twitter Board believed increased the lik=
elihood that the required debt and equity financing for the merger would be=
 available.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well. When they an=
nounced the deal,=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/27745071.259617/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbG=
